    <statement><p>Simplify the following expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain on the simplified expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{3t^{2}+t-2}{-5t-3-2t^{2}}}=}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{3t-2}{2t+3}, t\ne -1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cross out common factors:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{3t^{2}+t-2}{-5t-3-2t^{2}}} \amp = \frac{{\left(3t-2\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+1\right)}}{{-2t^{2}-5t-3}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{\left(3t-2\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+1\right)}}{{-\left(2t^{2}+5t+3\right)}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{\left(3t-2\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+1\right)}}{{-\left(2t+3\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+1\right)}} \\
                     \amp = {-\frac{3t-2}{2t+3}, t\ne -1}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>t+1</m> was crossed out, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>t \ne -1</m>.</p>
</solution>
